Cordillera del Cóndor region, upper Río Nangaritza. Las Orquídeas reserve, on west side of river. Tall, primary forest on steep slope above river, below sandstone plateau but with soil mostly derived from eroded sandstone. Canopy to 30 m with Chrysophyllum sanguineolentum dominant. One-hectare forest inventory plot; all trees > 10 cm DBH sampled, during dendrology course with students from Ecuador and Peru, funded by US National Science Foundation. Nangaritza River Plot.
